name":"Cathryn","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Katherine .  This form of the name is also used in France."]},{"name":"Cathrin","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Katherine .  This form of the name is also used in France."]},{"name":"Catharine","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Katherine .  This form of the name is also used in France."]}]},{"name":"verch","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Otto, Orlo.","German: variant of   Ferch  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Ferch","meanings":["German: variant of   Ferg  . Compare   Verch  .","Probably also an Americanized form of German <b>Förtsch</b> (see   Foertsch  ).","Probably also an Americanized form of German <b>Förch</b> (see   Foerch  )."]}]},{"name":"Thomas","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Bevon","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Transferred use of the surname, originally a nickname from Anglo-Norman French <i>jovene</i> ‘young’ (Latin <i>iuvenis</i>). Use as a given name has probably been influenced by its similarity in sound to   Evan ."],"variants":[{"name":"Jeavon","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Jevon ."]},{"name":"Jeevan","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Jevon ."]}]},{"name":"of","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Short form of   Oswald   or any of the various other names beginning with <i>Os-</i>."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Bryn","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["20th-century coinage from <i>bryn</i> ‘hill’; also a short form of   Brynmor ."],"variants":[{"name":"Brynn","meanings":["Mainly U.S.: respelling of Welsh Bryn . In the United States this is now used predominantly as a girl's name, perhaps by association with names such as   Lynn ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Catherine verch Thomas Bevon of Bryn was born in 1350, in Bryn, Glamorgan, Wales, her father, Thomas Bevon ap Leyson of Glamorgan, was 31 and her mother, Mrs Thomas Bevon ap Leyson, was 25. She married Hamon De Turberville about 1374, in Caernarfon, Caernarfonshire, Wales. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 2 daughters. She died in 1420, in Caernarfon, Caernarfonshire, Wales, at the age of 70."},"et":{"1350–1420":"1350–1420","1350–1425":"1350–1425","1374–1444":"1374–1444","1380–Male":"1380–Surnud","1398–Female":"1398–Surnud","1320–Male":"1320–Surnud","1325–Female":"1325–Surnud","1425":"1425","1325":"1325","1444":"1444","1398":"1398","1420":"1420","1320":"1320","1374":"1374","1350":"1350","about 1374":"umbes 1374","1380":"1380","Caernarfon, Caernarfonshire, Wales":"Caernarfon, Caernarfonshire, Wales","Tythegston, Mid Glamorganshire, Wales":"Tythegston, Mid Glamorgan, Wales, United Kingdom","Bryn, Glamorgan, Wales":"Bryn, Glamorgan, Wales","Tythegston, Glamorgan, Wales":"Tythegston, Glamorgan, Wales","Glamorgan, Wales":"Glamorgan, Wales","Caernarfon Castle, Caernarfon, Wales":"Caernarfon, Caernarfonshire, Wales"},"fi":{"1350–1420":"1350–1420","1350–1425":"1350–1425","1374–1444":"1374–1444","1380–Male":"1380–Kuollut","1398–Female":"1398–Kuollut","1320–Male":"1320–Kuollut","1325–Female":"1325–Kuollut","1425":"1425","1325":"1325","1444":"1444","1398":"1398","1420":"1420","1320":"1320","1374":"1374","1350":"1350","about 1374":"noin 1374","1380":"1380","C